text: Interior may refer to: ==Arts and media== * Interior (Degas) (also known as The Rape), painting by Edgar Degas * Interior (play), 1895 play by Belgian playwright Maurice Maeterlinck * The Interior (novel), by Lisa See * Interior design, the trade of designing an architectural interior ==Places== * Interior, South Dakota * Interior, Washington * Interior Township, Michigan * British Columbia Interior, commonly known as "The Interior" ==Government agencies== * Interior ministry, sometimes called the ministry of home affairs * United States Department of the Interior ==Other uses== * Interior (topology), mathematical concept that includes, for example, the inside of a shape * Interior FC, a football team in Gambia == Related pages == * *
